fr.insa.rennes.info.chemical.backend
Interface BuilderSubIndexProviderSolution

All Superinterfaces:
Builder<SubIndexProviderSolution>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BuilderSubIndexProviderSolutionImpl
interface BuilderSubIndexProviderSolution
extends Builder<SubIndexProviderSolution>

An interface specifying a builder for a SubIndexProviderSolution.
In order to follow the builder design pattern and for code reusability, an interface is used so that the implementation can be easily changed.

The only use of this builder is supposed to be in the BuilderIndexProvider. Indeed, an index provider possesses several SubIndexProvider, themselves recursively containing SubIndexProvider.The recursion ends on a SubIndexProviderElement. See IndexProvider documentation for more.

The different parameters of the builder are the solution, the reaction rule, the reaction rule's field, the parameterized type, and the SubSolution field. See the associated setters for a detailed descrition.
The only mandatory parameters are the solution and the reaction rule. You then have the choice between giving either the reaction rule's fields (see setReactionRuleFields(Field[])), or the parameterized type (setParamType(ParameterizedType) and the SubSolution field (setSubSolutionField(Field)). The first case is used to build the root SubIndexProviderSolution of a IndexProvider, and the second one is used to recursively build SubIndexProviderSolution.

Author:
Andréolli Cédric, Boulanger Chloé, Cléro Olivier, Guellier Antoine, Guilloux Sébastien, Templé Arthur

void setReactionRule(ReactionRule rr)
Sets the reaction rule parameter to build the sub index provider. The reaction rule parameter specifies which reaction rule needs reactives.

Parameters:

setReactionRuleFields

void setReactionRuleFields(java.lang.reflect.Field[] rrFields)
Sets the reaction rule's fields parameter to build the sub index provider. These fields are the reactives needed by the reaction rule. Basically, these are the attributes of the reaction rule class, without the ones annotated Dontreact.

Parameters:
rrFields - The reaction rule's fields
See Also:

setParamType

void setParamType(java.lang.reflect.ParameterizedType paramType)
Sets the parameterized type parameter to build the sub index provider. This type is the parameterized type of a SubSolution object. This SubSolution object is an attribute of the reaction rule given to the builder. This class is used to go down in the inner solutions of the reaction rule's main solution. See SubSolutionReactivesAccessor.

Parameters:
paramType - The parameterized type of a SubSolution object attribute of the specified reaction rule.
See Also:
SubSolution, SubSolutionReactivesAccessor

setSolution

void setSolution(Solution sol)
Sets the solution parameter to build the sub index provider. The specified solution is the solution in which the sub index provider has to rely to provide indexes on the reactives asked by the reaction rule parameter.

Parameters:
sol - The solution on which the sub index provider has to iterate.

setSubSolutionField

void setSubSolutionField(java.lang.reflect.Field subSolField)
Sets the SubSolution field parameter to build the sub index provider. This parameter is actually a field of the reaction rule parameter. See SubSolutionReactivesAccessor.

Parameters:
subSolField - The SubSolution field of the reaction rule.
